      "side": 1,
      "message": "```suggestion\n        warning(\"Failed to configure RS485 mode: {ERR}\", \"ERR\", strerror(err));\n\n```\n\nI have not observed this branch with either of the currently supported devices. xr_serial successfully applies TIOCSRS485, while ftdi_sio returns ENOTTY and works without kernel RS485 configuration.\nThe warning branch is currently defensive handling for other unexpected ioctl errors. Since we do not know whether every such error necessarily makes the device unusable, I am not certain that treating all of them as fatal is appropriate. If we want strict handling, we would need a way to know whether kernel RS485 configuration is mandatory for the specific device.",
